Review: The golden avocado mission style burrito is soooo good!! Nothing compared to burritos in SF imo still but honestly best burrito I’ve found in NY/NJ — the vegan chipotle aioli hits and the Habanero sauce is also really spicy and yummy

Overhyped! The paneer roll is okay but I don’t like the way they prepare the vegetables with the paneer — not trynna bite into a whole cherry tomato

I’d say thelewala on McDougall is 10 times better
Pretty solid kathi roll! Was a bit spicy! I’d say better then kathi roll company but not as good as Thelewala
They have a few veg options the bibimbap and tofu soup are both really really yummy! Def a better place for people who eat fish but still would come back

Got recommended this as a better version of Spicy Moon! From a vegetarian standpoint, they do have a lot of options and a pretty similar menu, but I do think spicy moon is significantly better.

Bonus star for the fact that they are open pretty late though

Lovee all the flavors — I’d say the ice cream runs sweeter than most places so if you don’t have a sweet tooth be warned

Got the mango and cream and it tasted exactly like mango ice cream in India
My fav vegan ramen in NYC! I love their delivery packaging everything comes so easy to assemble :) perfect for a rainy day

Basically another chipotle knockoff 

Bowl was okay, too much lettuce and they guac is not great..

The big thing they have going for them is that they have so many different sauces that were all really good!! The vegan chipotle aioli and the ghost pepper sauce were both fantastic would bottle those up and buy them individually for sure
MEXICAN PIZZA IS BACK LETS GOOOOOOOOOOOOOO
Ahhh such good vegan brunch! The French toast sticks were to die for and the chilaquiles were so good. So close to Union station too def gonna go every time I train into DC
Classsiccc late night post going out spot! Haven’t been in a long time, but got it again recently and the paneer bhurji with pav is so so so good

Another vegan spot worth checking out in NYC! I’m a pretty big fan of their bbq buffalo wings and the creole soul chicken! Personally always get those two appetizers and skip on the main courses. Sadly they were out of dessert today otherwise I would’ve been even more hyped
Honestly I’d go here again and again for the crispy okra dish! Other food was also pretty solid but a bit on the pricy side
Got the lime paneer and chatapata paneer rolls again today! Both fantastic, never disappointed by this place
Avocado tostada is chefs kiss wow so good fantastic quick lunch spot

So many vegetarian options and the food was all so good! The falafel pizza is a must, the labneh was really yummy as well as this eggplant dip dish that I’m forgetting the name of.

Love that they give a bunch of other sauces on the side as well as unlimited pita bread as well.

Only thing we got that I wouldn’t recommend were the fries
The frozen blended coffees are so so good and they have a huge menu of options on their website! Got Dutch bros every day for the week I was in Denton
Fine dining establishment
Had no idea what to expect from this but also had really heard high praise of this! They only had one vegetarian option but it was so so good and only 5 bucks! Def will visit again
Their wings are so yum! My cousins and I are obsessed ordered a tray of 50 for a Super Bowl party earlier

Fully vegan, Asian Mexican fusion!!!

The taco combination platter was amazing, my favorite one was the mango one.

The nachos were the star of the show!!! Pan fried gyoza as a nachos topping with guac and queso and sour cream worked so so surprisingly well. Would go back for those nachos
Ambiance is amazing, the food is also so so good! Love the stone pots dishes, and the scallion pancakes are also so good

This has been my all time favorite restaurant ever since I was in elementary school! The uncle and aunty that run this place are so so so nice and know me well. My go to dishes are the makhan malai paneer, the paneer wrap, or the paneer sizzler! Honestly a must go spot every time I come back home
Oof the blended coffee drinks here hit so well in 109 degree weather! The sizes here run large I couldn’t finish a medium
Not Shizen level but they had quite an extensive vegan menu! Most of the rolls were pretty good, the mushroom tempura one and the Thai one stood out to me the most

Honestly was pretty not vegetarian friendly compared to other Thai restaurants I’ve visited. Got the basil fried rice and the panang curry, both were average imo.

Other people I was with who got meat options really enjoyed the place

Their lunch prefix menu is an incredible deal and the food is actually so good! For vegetarians, 1 main dish + an app, naan, rice, and curry all for 15 bucks and the portions were honestly big enough for two meals for me
Oat milk soft serve!! It’s so so so creamy and the topping options make it even better :) would take this over regular soft serve anyday tbh
Paneer tikka pizza was pretty solid! Honestly better than most I’ve had in the Bay Area tbh
Almost as good as Taco Bell

Okay so had been super hyped to go to this place for a really long time.. vegan omakase like what

Pros: the food was very very simple and fresh and just felt healthy! All the courses were unique and the explanation that went with each dish made the experience. Had a really really great time (spent 3 hours there)

Cons: taste wise I felt like I wanted more! Maybe I was expecting something rich and decadent but in reality it was a really simple (but still elegant) meal.

Wish it was cheaper don’t know if I could justify paying that much for this experience again (unless I’m with amazing company!)

Oh my god… best vegan sushi I’ve had in my life second only to Shizen!

The Bollywood and the Mr. Crunch are MUST haves your life will actually be changed. Wish this place had a spot in NY beats anything that we have there
Got the falafel burger here and it was really really good! Made for a solid lunch and was fairly affordable. The patty was incredibly moist and the spicy sauce had a good kick
THEY HAVE A JAIN MENU!! Love taking my family here whenever I have relatives in town who eat jain. Also has a pretty filling lunch combo

Hands down my favorite restaurant in SF and the best vegan sushi I’ve experienced anywhere (Bloom sushi in Montreal is a close second)

I love going with a large group so we can get all of the specialty rolls, but my favorite roll is the body and soul! 

So sad I wasn’t able to stop by this trip but will be back for shizen in august

Okay this had been hyped up a lottttt for me but when I went I wasn’t sure what the best vegetarian option was so I got the Liang Pi Cold Skin noodles (A1) 

Honestly the noodles themselves were fantastic but it was a cold dish and the sauce was a bit too sour for my liking

If someone can Rec a better vegetarian dish here would try again but otherwise I don’t see the hype for vegetarians
Favorite Thai food in NYC! The lunch special is so worth it (app, soup, and main for like 14 bucks)
Monday night unlimited sushi is so worth it, I go like once a month. Favorite rolls are def the crispy rice and the torched and pressed :)
Used to be my go to spot post school in high school! Super large burritos for really cheap back than, giving them a 3 star now bc the price has gone up so much — burrito still tastes fire

Honestly it was good but not worth the price and the wait (granted I wasn’t the one who waited but still)

The calzone was better than the pizza imo, and the vibe and company was nice, but don’t fully understand the hype unfortunately :(
Not my favorite bagels in NYC tbh.. would walk the extra block and half to get Best Bagel or Liberty Bagels
A classic late night spot back home! Love the orange sauce
Food was super fresh and heavy on vegetables — def a fancy spot but would not come back again for the price personally.

Decent spot for vegan empanadas, have had better though!

Favorite empanada was probably the corn one or the apple cinnamon! Biggest complaint was that the empanadas had a lot more crust than filling and the crust was incredibly dry.

The garlic dipping sauce is super yummy though
Randomly dropped by here at 3 AM for food and hookah, service was so so nice and the freshly made Hadramout pita bread was some of the best pita I’ve ever has
Apparently pieology has a huge variety of different pizza doughs now! I tried the deep dish, but it was honestly just okay in my opinion
